{"cursor":"4057","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name = Robert Kirshner image = RobertKirshnerIMG 2728x.jpg birth_date = field\n| = Astrophysics work_institution = Harvard University alma_mater = Harvard\n| College (A.B.), California Institute of Technology (Ph.D.) known_for =\n| Type Ia Supernova Studies, Large Scale Structure, supernova remnants prizes =\n| Caltech Distinguished Alumni Award}}\n\n'Robert Kirshner' is the Clowes Professor of Science in the Harvard-Smithsonian\nCenter for Astrophysics at Harvard University. Kirshner has worked in several\nareas of astronomy including the physics of supernovae, supernova remnants, the\nLarge-scale structure of the cosmos, and the use of Supernovae to measure the\nexpansion of the universe.\n\nIn 1981, along with, Augustus Oemler, Jr., Paul Schechter, and Stephen Shectman,\nKirshner discovered the BoÃ¶tes void in a survey of galactic\nredshifts. Kirshner was a member of the High-z Supernova Search Team\nthat used observations of extragalactic supernovae to discover the accelerating\nuniverse. This universal acceleration implies the existence of dark energy and\nwas named the top science breakthrough of 1998 by Science magazine.\nFor this work he was jointly awarded the Gruber Cosmology Prize in 2007.\n\nHe is the author of The Extravagant Universe : Exploding Stars, Dark Energy, and\nthe Accelerating Cosmos (2002; ISBN 978-0-691-05862-7) and has been a member of\nthe National Academy of Sciences since 1998. He was the President of the\nAmerican Astronomical Society from 2004-2006.\n\nHe received his A.B. [[magna cum laude]] in Astronomy from Harvard College in\n1970, and his Ph.D., also in Astronomy, from Caltech. Prior to joining Harvard\nin 1985, he worked at Kitt Peak National Observatory and taught at the\nUniversity of Michigan for 9 years.\n\nHe was the co-Master of Quincy House, one of Harvard's 12 undergraduate houses,\nalong with his wife, Jayne Loader, before resigning in August 2007.\n\nHe is also the father of Rebecca Rand Kirshner.\n","linknr":149,"url":"Robert_Kirshner","recorded":1375088695,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Robert_Kirshner&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Robert_Kirshner&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png","/wiki/Wikipedia:Biographies_of_living_persons","/wiki/Wikipedia:Citing_sources","/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability","/wiki/Wikipedia:Reliable_sources","/wiki/Defamation","/wiki/File:RobertKirshnerIMG_2728x.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d7/RobertKirshnerIMG_2728x.jpg/220px-RobertKirshnerIMG_2728x.jpg","/wiki/Harvard_University","/wiki/Alma_mater","/wiki/Harvard_College","/wiki/Bachelors_of_Arts","/wiki/California_Institute_of_Technology","/wiki/Ph.D.","/wiki/Supernova","/wiki/Supernova_remnant","/wiki/Center_for_Astrophysics","/wiki/Harvard_University","/wiki/Astronomy","/wiki/Supernova","/wiki/Supernova_remnant","/wiki/Large-scale_structure_of_the_cosmos","/wiki/Supernova","/wiki/Paul_L._Schechter","/wiki/Bo%C3%B6tes_void","#cite_note-1","/wiki/High-z_Supernova_Search_Team","/wiki/Supernovae","/wiki/Accelerating_universe","/wiki/Dark_energy","#cite_note-2","